parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in heavy rain or snow.
symptoms: The wipers slow down or stop after a short period of time (45-80 seconds)
requiring the driver to turn them off and on again to restore functionality; wipers operate at an inadequate speed
